    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2fb65dd5_da7dfb18",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/car.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 77,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-14T22:37:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Generally we prefer to add new raw pipe services instead of using Qemud. Qemud was created originally to abstract out two interfaces: old serial port and new qemu pipe. Now, when nobody uses emulated serial ports for communication, qemud mostly adds unneeded overhead to the services.\nConsider writing a raw pipe service if you expect any performance-critical or latency-critical communication here.\nYou can take a look at Opengl pipe or AdbGuestPipe as an example",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 77,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 77,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "ea0662f6cf29a20743d6da1723388afee20ba1c6",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e33cc049_bb0a9df9",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/car.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 77,
      "author": {
        "id": 1061217
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-14T23:21:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this pipe service is for communicating car data (e.g., gear, speed, hardware key event), which is very compact and only for manual testing through UI.  Performance and latency are not big issues here. Can I keep the qemud implementation? Or do you prefer me to switch to raw pipe?",
      "parentUuid": "2fb65dd5_da7dfb18",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 77,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 77,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "ea0662f6cf29a20743d6da1723388afee20ba1c6",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2cd0ec1b_a7c21047",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/car.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 77,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-14T23:27:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sure then. Qemud adds some framing overhead, it also needs to allocate separate buffers to hold the data before sending etc. If you send big and fast (as GPU virtualization), it\u0027s won\u0027t work. For anything simple it\u0027s OK.",
      "parentUuid": "e33cc049_bb0a9df9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 77,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 77,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "ea0662f6cf29a20743d6da1723388afee20ba1c6",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
